SIMPLE: particularly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Particularly
<hw>Par*tic"u*lar*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a
particular manner; expressly; with a specific reference or interest; in
particular; distinctly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In an especial manner; especially; in a high degree;
<as>as, a <ex>particularly</ex> fortunate man; a <ex>particularly</ex>
bad failure.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The exact propriety of <person>Virgil I</person>
<qex>particularly</qex> regarded as a great part of his character.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Particularment</ent>⟦br⟧
